%----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%	OBJECTIVES
%----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
\vspace{-20mm}
\begin{alertblock}{\textbf{GOALS}}
The main goal was to build a translator software, which could be used in educational software, to help mute and not hearing people to improve their English literacy skills. To achieve this goal the following tasks were implemented.
\begin{itemize}
\item Visual Studio \textbf{(VS) 2013} and \textbf{WPF} structure were used to integrate the \textbf{Kinect and Leap Motion (LM) APIs} capabilities, and create the user interface (UI).
\vspace{5mm}
\item \textbf{Upper-body and hands features} were extracted and converted into matrices for comparison. The \textbf{UI} created in the VS 2013 generates \textbf{feature matrices} and \textbf{saves preliminary data} for training.
\vspace{5mm}
\item A \textbf{chain of matrices} and a \textbf{matrix similarity} algorithm serve as support vector machines (SVM). \textbf{Segments conditions} serve as a Hidden Markov Model (HMM) to \textbf{translate ASL to text}.
\end{itemize}

\end{alertblock}

